<entry>
            <title><![CDATA[Who do we spend time with across our lifetime?]]></title>
            <id>https://ourworldindata.org/time-with-others-lifetime</id>
            <link rel="alternate" href="https://ourworldindata.org/time-with-others-lifetime"/>
            <published>2020-12-11T11:00:00.000Z</published>
            <updated>2020-12-15T21:02:35.000Z</updated>
            <author><name>Esteban Ortiz-Ospina</name></author>
            <summary><![CDATA[In adolescence we spend the most time with our parents, siblings, and friends; as we enter adulthood we spend more time with our co-workers, partners, and children; and in our later years we spend an increasing amount of time alone.<br><br><a href="https://ourworldindata.org/time-with-others-lifetime" target="_blank"><img src="https://ourworldindata.org/app/uploads/2020/12/time-spent-with-relationships-by-age-us-768x403.png"/></a>]]></summary>
            </entry>
