            <title><![CDATA[The world’s energy problem]]></title>
            <id>https://ourworldindata.org/worlds-energy-problem</id>
            <link rel="alternate" href="https://ourworldindata.org/worlds-energy-problem"/>
            <published>2020-12-10T11:00:00.000Z</published>
            <updated>2020-12-15T13:37:29.000Z</updated>
            <author><name>Max Roser</name></author>
            <summary><![CDATA[The world faces two energy problems: most of our energy production still produces greenhouse gas emissions, and hundreds of millions lack access to energy entirely.<br><br><a href="https://ourworldindata.org/worlds-energy-problem" target="_blank"><img src="https://ourworldindata.org/app/uploads/2020/11/Screen-Shot-2020-11-26-at-10.33.19-768x428.png"/></a>]]></summary>
            </entry>
<entry>
            <title><![CDATA[How do people across the world spend their time and what does this tell us about living conditions?]]></title>
            <id>https://ourworldindata.org/time-use-living-conditions</id>
            <link rel="alternate" href="https://ourworldindata.org/time-use-living-conditions"/>
            <published>2020-12-08T10:04:00.000Z</published>
            <updated>2020-12-15T21:03:41.000Z</updated>
            <author><name>Esteban Ortiz-Ospina</name></author>
            <summary><![CDATA[How people spend their time is similar in many ways across countries: we all sleep, work, eat, and enjoy leisure. But there are also important differences in the freedom people have to spend time on the things they value most.<br><br><a href="https://ourworldindata.org/time-use-living-conditions" target="_blank"><img src="https://ourworldindata.org/app/uploads/2020/12/thumbnailTime-Use-by-Country-OECD-768x402.png"/></a>]]></summary>
            </entry>
